# Music-core REST API (Assignment 2 bronze)
# Use with VS Code REST Client, IntelliJ HTTP Client, or copy curl examples.
# Default: API on port 3001. With Vite dev, you can use http://localhost:5173 (proxied).

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

### Health (also used before WebSocket connect in the client)
GET {{baseUrl}}/health

### Listings — paginated list with filters
GET {{baseUrl}}/listings?page=1&pageSize=6&category=Accessories&search=guitar

### Listings — by id
GET {{baseUrl}}/listings/listing_1

### Listings — create
POST {{baseUrl}}/listings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "REST Client Test Listing",
  "description": "Created via rest-api.http for Assignment 2 demonstration.",
  "price": 499,
  "category": "Accessories",
  "photos": ["https://picsum.photos/seed/rest-client/1200/900"],
  "sellerId": "user_1"
}

### Listings — update (replace listingId)
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/listings/listing_REPLACE_ME
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "status": "Sold",
  "price": 550
}

### Listings — delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/listings/listing_REPLACE_ME

### Statistics — summary
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats/summary

### Statistics — categories
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats/categories

### Statistics — top sellers
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats/sellers?limit=5

### Statistics — favourites breakdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats/favourites

### Statistics — reviews breakdown
GET {{baseUrl}}/stats/reviews

### Reviews — list for listing
GET {{baseUrl}}/listings/listing_1/reviews

### Reviews — create
POST {{baseUrl}}/listings/listing_1/reviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "listingId": "listing_1",
  "userId": "user_2",
  "rating": 5,
  "title": "Great gear",
  "body": "Exactly as described."
}

### Reviews — update
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/reviews/review_REPLACE_ME
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "rating": 4,
  "body": "Updated review text."
}

### Reviews — delete
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/reviews/review_REPLACE_ME

### Favourites — list for user
GET {{baseUrl}}/favourites?userId=user_1

### Favourites — add
POST {{baseUrl}}/favourites
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "user_1",
  "listingId": "listing_2"
}

### Favourites — remove
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/favourites/listing_2?userId=user_1

### Auth — login
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "alex@musiccore.local",
  "password": "RiffMaster123!"
}

### Auth — register
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "rest_demo_user",
  "email": "rest.demo@musiccore.test",
  "password": "password123"
}

### Generator — start
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/generate/start
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "batchSize": 2,
  "intervalMs": 2000,
  "entityType": "listings"
}

### Generator — stop
POST {{baseUrl}}/admin/generate/stop
